=== Chick-lit
protagonist often femal and relatable
most important - journey and growth
romance-optional
often urban and modern
inspired by a discontent with the unattainability of contemporary women's literature
- protagonist
    love interest
    empowerment
    meet-cute
    workaholic
    rom-com: like chick-lit, but with less of a focus on female protagonist and more on romance
    beakup
    miscommunication
    bridget joens-esque: flawed yet lovable female character in 20s-30s with witty and self-deprecating demeanor
- mommy lit
    chick lit jr
    chick lit in corsets
- the devil wears prada
    bridget jones's diary
    the notebook
    the love hypothesis
    the uhoneymooners
    confessions of a shopaholic
chick-flick: chick-lit but original movie
